{
  "title": "Future with Going To - Plans and Intentions",
  "description": "Learn how to express future plans and intentions using 'going to', including structure, usage, vocabulary, and practice exercises.",
  "image": "https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2016/01/19/17/47/signpost-1148983_1280.jpg",
  "mainTag": "grammar-beginner",
  "elements": [
    {
      "type": "explanation",
      "subtitle": "Understanding 'Going To' for Future Plans",
      "order": 0,
      "explanation": [
        {
          "title": "📌 What is 'Going To'?",
          "image": "https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2015/07/31/20/39/road-sign-869234_1280.jpg",
          "list": [
            "'Going to' is used to talk about plans or intentions for the future.",
            "It shows that a decision has already been made before the moment of speaking.",
            "It can also describe something we expect to happen based on evidence."
          ]
        },
        {
          "title": "🧱 Structure",
          "image": "https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2014/04/02/14/10/diagram-306789_1280.png",
          "list": [
            "Affirmative: Subject + am/is/are + going to + base verb",
            "Negative: Subject + am/is/are + not + going to + base verb",
            "Question: Am/Is/Are + subject + going to + base verb?"
          ]
        },
        {
          "title": "🧠 When to Use",
          "image": "https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2017/05/10/17/28/calendar-2309223_1280.png",
          "list": [
            "To talk about future plans: 'I am going to visit my grandparents next week.'",
            "To make predictions based on evidence: 'Look at those clouds! It’s going to rain.'"
          ]
        },
        {
          "title": "⚠️ Common Mistakes",
          "image": "https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2013/07/12/19/20/warning-154550_1280.png",
          "list": [
            "Don't forget to use the correct form of 'to be' before 'going to'.",
            "Remember that 'going to' is not the same as 'will' in all situations."
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "subtitle": "Future Plans Vocabulary",
      "order": 1,
      "sentences": [
        { "english": "Plan", "portuguese": "Plano" },
        { "english": "Trip", "portuguese": "Viagem" },
        { "english": "Meet", "portuguese": "Encontrar" },
        { "english": "Visit", "portuguese": "Visitar" },
        { "english": "Move", "portuguese": "Mudar-se" },
        { "english": "Start", "portuguese": "Começar" },
        { "english": "Finish", "portuguese": "Terminar" },
        { "english": "Work", "portuguese": "Trabalhar" },
        { "english": "Study", "portuguese": "Estudar" },
        { "english": "Celebrate", "portuguese": "Celebrar" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "sentences",
      "subtitle": "Plans in Context",
      "order": 2,
      "sentences": [
        {
          "english": "I am going to visit my grandparents this weekend.",
          "portuguese": "Eu vou visitar meus avós neste fim de semana."
        },
        {
          "english": "They are going to start a new project at work.",
          "portuguese": "Eles vão começar um novo projeto no trabalho."
        },
        {
          "english": "She is going to move to a bigger apartment.",
          "portuguese": "Ela vai se mudar para um apartamento maior."
        },
        {
          "english": "We are going to celebrate our anniversary next month.",
          "portuguese": "Nós vamos celebrar nosso aniversário no próximo mês."
        },
        {
          "english": "He is going to study for the final exam.",
          "portuguese": "Ele vai estudar para o exame final."
        },
        {
          "english": "I am going to finish my homework before dinner.",
          "portuguese": "Eu vou terminar minha lição de casa antes do jantar."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "exercise",
      "subtitle": "Comprehension Questions",
      "order": 3,
      "items": [
        "What does 'going to' express?",
        "How do you form the affirmative structure?",
        "How do you form the negative structure?",
        "How do you form questions with 'going to'?",
        "Give one example of a plan using 'going to'.",
        "Give one example of a prediction using 'going to'.",
        "When do we use 'going to' instead of 'will'?",
        "What is the correct form of 'to be' for 'I'?",
        "What is the correct form of 'to be' for 'they'?",
        "Mention one common mistake with 'going to'."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "exercise",
      "subtitle": "Translate into English",
      "order": 4,
      "items": [
        "Eu vou visitar meus avós no domingo.",
        "Eles vão começar um novo projeto.",
        "Ela vai se mudar para outra cidade.",
        "Nós vamos celebrar nosso aniversário.",
